        SAY_PERHAPS_YOU_COULD_CHECK_MY_STORY_OUT                                  = 8432,  -- Say, perhaps you could check my story out, and go see if the facts match up before you submitaru it to him? Maybe you could also get a few other adventurers to help you out and serve as witnesses...?
        TO_FINISH_YOUR_JOB_BY_CONFIRMING_MY_NEWS                                  = 8433,  -- To finish your job by confirming my news scoop, head into the depths of the eastern magic tower and find out whether the Cat Burglar's hideaway really does existaru there.
        I_DON_TARU_SUGGEST_THAT_YOU_ACTUALLY_GO                                   = 8434,  -- I don'taru suggest that you actually go inside her hideaway, as the Cat Burglar is bound to have dangerous traps and guards there. Just find the entrance to the place at the back of the Horutoto Ruins...then get the hell outta there!
        I_KNEW_IT_MY_SOURCES_WERE_CORRECTARU_RACE                                 = 8435,  -- I knew it! My sources were correctaru! Race on back to my editor with the scoop before someone else beats us to it!
        THIS_YEAR_S_PULITZER_BULITZER_PRIZE_FOR_JOURNALISM                        = 8436,  -- This year's Pulitzer-Bulitzer Prize for journalism is in my pocket for sure! I'll make sure I thank you in my acceptance speech!
        THE_CAT_BURGLAR_WURGLAR_OH_YOU_MEAN_NANAA                                 = 8437,  -- The Cat Burglar-wurglar...? Oh, you mean Nanaa Mihgo? Of course I know her!
        THEY_SAY_THE_TREASURES_SHE_STEALS_FROM_PEOPLE                             = 8438,  -- They say the treasures she steals from people are never-ever found again. That's why the Mithra guardy-wardies can never arrest her...there's just no proof!
        AS_I_THOUGHTARU_I_WON_THIS_YEAR_S                                         = 8439,  -- As I thoughtaru! I won this year's Pulitzer-Bulitzer Prize for journalism with my scoop on the Cat Burglar!
        AND_IT_S_ALL_THANKS_TO_YOU_FOR                                            = 8440,  -- And it's all thanks to you for helping confirm that it was true. I really want to thank you more, but will this do...?
        I_CAN_TARU_WAIT_TO_SEE_OUR_NEXT                                           = 8441,  -- I can'taru wait to see our next exclusive issue.
        MY_EXPOS_I_WILL_BE_THE_TOP_STORY                                          = 8442,  -- My expos%i will be the top story for sure. But I can'taru rest on my laurels. A good reporter has to keep following the truth, as no story ever really ends.
        CAN_T_YOU_SEE_I_M_BUSY_NOW_2                                              = 8443,  -- Can't you see I'm busy now? Give a girl a little brrreathing room, huh?
        YOU_DID_PUT_THE_YOU_KNOW_WHAT_INTO                                        = 8444,  -- You did put the you-know-what into a metal box and sink it in the sea as we were told to, didn't you?
        YOU_VE_GOT_A_CAT_S_CHANCE_IN                                              = 8445,  -- You've got a cat's chance in hell of getting me to steal something like that again! Next time, you do the stealing, and I do the sinking, okay?
        OO_H_AA_H_OU_CH_I_DON                                                     = 8446,  -- Oo`h... Aa`h... Ou`ch...! I don't think our last burrrglary was such a good idea. The wounds where I was bitten by the you-know-what still ache, not to mention my back from carrying that heavy box I put it in.
        WHAT_DO_YOU_MEAN_MY_SCOOP_EXPOS_I                                         = 8447,  -- What do you mean, my scoop expos%i has been stolen!?
        THAT_DIRTY_ROTTEN_LOW_DOWN_CAT_BURGLAR_SHE                                = 8448,  -- That dirty, rotten, low-down Cat Burglar! She's made a preemptive strike so as not to be caught outaru. This is a cat-astrophe!
        LOOKS_LIKE_THIS_WEEK_S_EDITION_OF_THE                                     = 8449,  -- Looks like this week's edition of the Tarutaru Times's Magic Paradise Weekly is going to be canceled as well.
        IF_I_SAID_IT_ONCE_I_VE_SAID                                               = 8450,  -- If I said it once, I've said it a thousand times... We should give up on using those silly magic dolls to deliver our stories. and go back to the tried and true method of newspapers and magazines! Our stories always end up never getting told.
