        I_AM_TAPOH_LIHZEH_THE_APOTHECARRRY_IS_THERE                               = 8556,  -- I am Tapoh Lihzeh the apothecarrry. Is there something you want from me, or are you looking for my daughterrr?
        IF_YOU_ARE_AFTER_MY_DAUGHTERRR_THEN_I                                     = 8557,  -- If you are after my daughterrr, then I suggest you head overrr to Windurst Waters. She's studying at the School of Magic there.
        FROM_HUMBLE_MITHRAN_COLD_MEDICINES_TO_THE_LEGENDARY                       = 8558,  -- From humble Mithran cold medicines to the legendary Windurstian ambrrrosia of immortality, we have it all...
        PSST_HEY_YOU_YES_YOU_THERE                                                = 8559,  -- Psst! Hey, you... Yes, you there!
        YOU_LIKE_THE_TYPE_OF_GUY_GAL_WHO                                          = 8560,  -- You like the type of guy/gal] who'd be interested in my secret cache of wares. Wanna have a little look?
        PSST_INTERESTED_IN_SOME_RRREAL_HOT_PROPERTY_FROM                          = 8561,  -- Psst... Interested in some rrreal hot property? From lucky chocobo digs to bargain goods that fell off the back of an airship...all my stuff is a rrreal steal!
        YOU_RE_INTERESTED_IN_SOME_CHEAP_SHOPPING_RRRIGHT                          = 8562,  -- You're interested in some cheap shopping, rrright? I'm real sorry. I'm not doing business rrright now.
        LADIES_AND_GENTLEMEN_KITTENS_AND_CUBS_DO_WE                               = 8563,  -- Ladies and gentlemen, kittens and cubs! Do we have the sale that you've been waiting forrr!
        SORRY_BUT_OUR_SHOP_IS_CLOSED_RRRIGHT_NOW                                  = 8564,  -- Sorry, but our shop is closed rrright now. Why don't you go to Gustaberg and help the situation out therrre?
        WHY_DON_T_YOU_BUY_SOMETHING_FROM_ME                                       = 8565,  -- Why don't you buy something from me? You won't regrrret it! I've got all sorts of goods from the Zulkheim region!
        I_M_TAKING_A_BRRREAK_FROM_THE_SALESWOMAN                                  = 8566,  -- I'm taking a brrreak from the saleswoman gig to give dirrrections. So...through this arrrch is the residential area.
        OOH_DO_I_HAVE_SOME_GREAT_MERCHANDISE_FOR                                  = 8567,  -- Ooh...do I have some great merchandise for you! Man...these are once-in-a-lifetime offers, so get them while you can.
        PANT_I_AM_BUT_A_POOR_MERCHANT_MATE                                        = 8568,  -- <pant> I am but a poor merchant. Mate, but you just wait! Strife...one day I'll live the high life. Hey, that's my dream, anyway...
        YES_THIS_IS_THE_CONSULATE_OF_SAN_D                                        = 8569,  -- Yes. This is the consulate of San d'Oria. How may I be of service?
        I_SEE_YOU_HAVE_NO_BUSINESS_WITH_ME                                        = 8570,  -- I see... You have no business with me. Sorry, but I have work I must return to, so please allow me to continue with it. Good day.
        IF_I_MAY_ALLOW_ME_TO_TELL_YOU                                             = 8571,  -- If I may, allow me to tell you a little about San d'Oria...
        SAN_D_ORIA_IS_A_LAND_OF_THE                                               = 8572,  -- San d'Oria is a land of the sword and of great faith. It is famous for its gallant Royal Knights and loyal Temple Knights, its grand regal chateau, and its glorious cathedral.
        THE_HYMNS_SUNG_IN_THE_CATHEDRAL_ARE_PARTICULARLY                          = 8573,  -- The hymns sung in the cathedral are particularly divine. Even the stoniest of hearts cannot help but be moved by them.
        IT_IS_RATHER_IMPOSSIBLE_TO_SAY_THAT_THE                                   = 8574,  -- It is rather impossible to say that the Windurstian government is the most logical system. However, the Tarutaru believe in their Star Sibyl and maintain strong bonds with each other.
        AND_IS_IT_NOT_THE_FAITH_AND_THE                                           = 8575,  -- And is it not the faith and the bonds of its citizens that make a country strong? Only when the hearts of the individuals are unified can a government really work.
        THIS_IS_THE_CONSULATE_OF_SAN_D_ORIA                                       = 8576,  -- This is the consulate of San d'Oria. Our role is to serve and protect the citizens of San d'Oria residing in Windurst.
        BUT_OF_COURSE_WE_SHAN_T_FORSAKE_NON                                       = 8577,  -- But of course, we shan't forsake non-San d'Orian citizens who require our assistance. For we San d'Orians are indeed a just people.
        THE_LIGHT_SHINES_WHERE_THERE_IS_RIGHTEOUSNESS_SO                          = 8578,  -- The light shines where there is righteousness, so do not be afraid, citizen of [San d'Oria/Bastok/Windurst]. The soldiers of San d'Oria only unsheathe their swords in the name of justice.
        THE_LIGHT_SHINES_ONLY_WHERE_THERE_IS_RIGHTEOUSNESS                        = 8579,  -- The light shines only where there is righteousness. Fellow citizen of San d'Oria, never lose the pride you have in your country.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_CONSULATE_OF_SAN_D_ORIA                                    = 8580,  -- Welcome to the consulate of San d'Oria. If you wish to speak to Consul Mourices, enter his office through the door on your right.
        SO_YOU_VE_COME_ALL_THE_WAY_FROM                                           = 8581,  -- So you've come all the way from San d'Oria, eh? Your dedication to serving the motherland is most admirable.
        UNFORTUNATELY_I_AM_IN_ONE_OF_MY_MOODS                                     = 8582,  -- Unfortunately, I am in one of my moods today. After I read the mission request from Windurst, I became most disgusted.
        FORINE_PLEASE_EXPLAIN_TO_THE_BRAVE_MAN_NICE                               = 8583,  -- Forine, please explain to the brave man/nice lady] here what the mission entails.
        YES_CONSUL_ALLOW_ME_TO_EXPLAIN                                            = 8584,  -- Yes, Consul. Allow me to explain...
        THE_MISSION_FROM_THE_WINDURSTIAN_GOVERNMENT_ENTAILS_THE                   = 8585,  -- The mission from the Windurstian government entails the oblation of magic armor to Giddeus, the frontline to the abode of the Yagudo beastmen.
        A_MAGIC_SHIELD_WILL_BE_HANDED_TO_YOU                                      = 8586,  -- A magic shield will be handed to you at Heavens Tower in Windurst Walls. Your orders are to deliver it to the Yagudo treasure chamber, deep in the underground of Giddeus.
        HAVE_YOU_HAD_THE_MISFORTUNE_OF_MEETING_THE                                = 8587,  -- Have you had the misfortune of meeting the Yagudo yet? They have made a nasty practice out of ganging up to attack the travelers who pass through Sarutabaruta...
        THESE_ARE_THE_SAME_BEASTMEN_WHO_SIDED_WITH                                = 8588,  -- These are the same beastmen who sided with the Kindred twenty years ago, and killed many of our comrades in the war.
        HOWEVER_THE_WINDURSTIANS_HAVE_GROWN_TOO_COMPLACENT_AND                    = 8589,  -- However, the Windurstians have grown too complacent and show their love of pacifism--even if it is nothing more than a one-sided fa%gade--by forming amicable relations with the Yagudo beastmen.
        AND_NOW_THEY_DARE_ASK_US_PROUD_SAN                                        = 8590,  -- And now they dare ask us proud San d'Orians to carry a tribute to a pack of beastmen. It would almost be laughable if it wasn't such a slap in the face.
        HOWEVER_THIS_MISSION_HAS_TO_BE_ACCOMPLISHED_AS                            = 8591,  -- However, this mission has to be accomplished as part of our pledge to Windurst. We Elvaan are not ones to break our promises, are we?
        AND_YET_AT_THE_SAME_TIME_AS_SAN                                           = 8592,  -- And yet, at the same time, as San d'Orians, we cannot allow this injustice to go unchecked.
        THE_SITUATION_IS_MOST_EXASPERATING_HOWEVER_I_MUST                         = 8593,  -- The situation is most exasperating. However, I must command you to go and give the Yagudo their magic shield. But at the same time, I entreat you to deprive the other Yagudo you meet along the way of two of their shields, making up for the imbalance.
        NOW_OFF_WITH_YOU                                                          = 8594,  -- Now, off with you!
        HOWEVER_EXASPERATING_THE_SITUATION_I_MUST_COMMAND_YOU                     = 8595,  -- However exasperating the situation, I must command you to go give the Yagudo their magic shield. At the same time, I entreat you to deprive the Yagudo you meet along the way twice the number of the shields to make up for the imbalance.
        NO_ELVAAN_WOULD_EVER_DO_SOMETHING_AS_DISHONORABLE                         = 8596,  -- No Elvaan would ever do something as dishonorable as breaking a promise to another.
        YOUR_ORDERS_ARE_TO_PROCEED_TO_HEAVENS_TOWER                               = 8597,  -- Your orders are to proceed to Heavens Tower in Windurst Walls, where a magic shield will be handed to you.
        IN_ORDER_TO_ACCOMPLISH_THIS_MISSION_AS_ASSIGNED                           = 8598,  -- In order to accomplish this mission as assigned by Windurst, you are to deliver the shield to the Yagudo treasure chamber, deep underground in Giddeus. However, that is not all...
        WHILE_WE_CANNOT_BREAK_OUR_PROMISE_TO_THE                                  = 8599,  -- While we cannot break our promise to the Windurstians, to ensure justice is served, we would secretly like you to take two shields off of the Yagudo who you meet en route.
        ACT_ACCORDING_TO_OUR_CONVICTIONS_WHILE_FULFILLING_OUR                     = 8600,  -- Act according to our convictions while fulfilling our promise with the Tarutaru. This is indeed a fitting course for us, the people of glorious San d'Oria.
        FOOL_DID_YOU_NOT_HEAR_OUR_ORDERS_CORRECTLY                                = 8601,  -- Fool! Did you not hear our orders correctly? Or are you just out to start a war?
        CAN_YOU_NOT_REMEMBER_THE_MOST_IMPORTANT_PART                              = 8602,  -- Can you not remember the most important part of the mission? You had to deliver a magic shield to the Yagudo treasure chamber. And you call yourself a San d'Orian!?
        FOOL                                                                      = 8603,  -- Fool!
        YOU_ONLY_HANDED_OVER_WINDURST_S_MAGIC_SHIELD                              = 8604,  -- You only handed over Windurst's magic shield to the Yagudo and skipped back, leaving the balance of power skewed. Such action would be considered treason back in San d'Oria!!!
        HUMPH_SEEMS_AS_IF_YOU_WERE_ABLE_TO                                        = 8605,  -- Humph. Seems as if you were able to maintain the path of righteousness.
        YOU_ARE_NOW_TO_HEAD_TO_THE_CONSULATE                                      = 8606,  -- You are now to head to the Consulate of San d'Oria in Bastok.
        DO_YOU_KNOW_THE_WAY_TO_BASTOK_FROM                                        = 8607,  -- Do you know the way to Bastok from here? You can travel by sea from Mhaura back to Selbina. From there, you have to cross the highlands to the south.
        GLORY_TO_THE_KINGDOM_OF_SAN_D_ORIA                                        = 8608,  -- Glory to the Kingdom of San d'Oria. Farewell and safe passage.
        HEAD_TO_THE_CONSULATE_OF_SAN_D_ORIA                                       = 8609,  -- Head to the Consulate of San d'Oria in Bastok.
        THE_BEST_WAY_TO_JOURNEY_TO_BASTOK_FROM                                    = 8610,  -- The best way to journey to Bastok from here is to ride a ship from Mhaura back to Selbina. From there, you have to cross the highlands to the south.
        THE_REPUBLIC_OF_BASTOK_IS_OCCUPIED_BY_TWO                                 = 8611,  -- The Republic of Bastok is occupied by two races, the Hume and the Galka, who are the exact antithesis of each other.
        OCCASIONALLY_THEY_BREAK_OUT_INTO_FIGHTS_SO_IT                             = 8612,  -- Occasionally they break out into fights, so it is imperative that you maintain neutrality as you assess the situation and then avail yourself to the righteous ones.
        NOW_THAT_YOU_HAVE_COMPLETED_THAT_LITTLE_MISSION                           = 8613,  -- Now that you have completed that little mission of amity, you are just an ordinary San d'Orian citizen again. So that frees you to go to Giddeus and really give those beastmen what they deserve.
        HOWEVER_WE_SHAN_T_TAKE_RESPONSIBILITY_IF_YOU                              = 8614,  -- However, we shan't take responsibility if you get seriously hurt in the process.
        YOUR_EFFORTS_ARE_WELL_NOTED_TAKE_CARE_ON                                  = 8615,  -- Your efforts are well noted. Take care on your journey to Bastok.
        SO_YOU_VE_COME_ALL_THE_WAY_FROM_2                                         = 8616,  -- So you've come all the way from San d'Oria, eh? Your dedication to serving the motherland is most admirable.
        THIS_MISSION_ON_THE_BEHALF_OF_THE_WINDURSTIAN                             = 8617,  -- This mission on the behalf of the Windurstian government displays our country's level of friendship towards Windurst.
        FORINE_PLEASE_EXPLAIN_TO_THE_BRAVE_MAN_NICE_2                             = 8618,  -- Forine, please explain to the brave man/nice lady] here what the mission entails.
        YES_CONSUL_ALLOW_ME_TO_EXPLAIN_WINDURST_S                                 = 8619,  -- Yes, Consul. Allow me to explain Windurst's request...
        A_GIANT_MONSTER_HAS_APPEARED_IN_THE_DEPTHS                                = 8620,  -- A giant monster has appeared in the depths of Giddeus, the borderland to the theocracy of the Yagudo beastmen. The Windurstian government wants it exterminated.
        YOU_ARE_TO_RECEIVE_A_KEY_FROM_HEAVENS                                     = 8621,  -- You are to receive a key from Heavens Tower in the Windurst Walls district and head to the innermost part of Giddeus, where the creature awaits.
        HA_HA_WHAT_A_JOLLY_TALE_THAT_IS                                           = 8622,  -- Ha-ha! What a jolly tale that is. A ferocious monster appearing in the heart of Giddeus, scaring the Yagudo so much they ask Tarutaru to help them?
        IT_S_MOST_FORTUNATE_FOR_THOSE_BEASTMEN_THAT                               = 8623,  -- It's most fortunate for those beastmen that the Windurst government had sought amicable relations with them in order to maintain the peace of their country.
        WHAT_DON_T_TELL_ME_YOU_HADN_T                                             = 8624,  -- What? Don't tell me you hadn't heard of Windurst's little peace pact with the Yagudo?
        OF_COURSE_WE_SAN_D_ORIANS_HAVE_NO                                         = 8625,  -- Of course, we San d'Orians have no need to show to those vulgar beastmen any courtesy whatsoever, but this is an agreement between our two countries, so we have no choice but to go through with it.
        SO_GO_AHEAD_AND_EXTERMINATE_THE_FEROCIOUS_MONSTER                         = 8626,  -- So go ahead and exterminate the ferocious monster plaguing the depths of Giddeus, but don't think you have to hold back from also giving those whining beastmen what they deserve.
        ANYWAY_ENOUGH_CHATTER_GODSPEED_ON_YOUR_ASSIGNMENT                         = 8627,  -- Anyway, enough chatter. Godspeed on your assignment.
        GO_AND_EXTERMINATE_THE_FEROCIOUS_MONSTER_PLAGUING_THE                     = 8628,  -- Go and exterminate the ferocious monster plaguing the depths of Giddeus, but don't hold back from also giving those whining beastmen what they deserve.
        TO_ACCESS_THE_INNERMOST_PART_OF_GIDDEUS_YOU                               = 8629,  -- To access the innermost part of Giddeus, you must receive the key from Heavens Tower in the Windurst Walls district.
        REPORT_BACK_HERE_ONCE_YOU_HAVE_DEFEATED_THE                               = 8630,  -- Report back here once you have defeated the ferocious monster that is menacing the Yagudo in the depths of Giddeus.
        I_WOULD_NOT_TRY_TO_DENY_THE_TARUTARU                                      = 8631,  -- I would not try to deny the Tarutaru of this land from pursuing peace. It is just that I desire lasting peace, not the temporary fa%gade that Windurst has now.
        THE_APPARENT_TRANQUILITY_OF_THIS_PLACE_CAN_BE                             = 8632,  -- The apparent tranquility of this place can be considered an illusion born from idealism. Until we wake Windurst from its dream it will continue to be beyond help.
        BECOMING_A_SOLDIER_IS_A_COMPLETELY_DIFFERENT_WAY                          = 8633,  -- Becoming a soldier is a completely different way of life than being a mere fighter.
        YOU_ARE_CAUGHT_BETWEEN_INTRICATE_ORDERS_AND_CHIVALRY                      = 8634,  -- You are caught between intricate orders and chivalry, and sometimes you have to go against your personal convictions...
        WHAT_IS_THIS_YOU_SPEAK_THE_SHADOW_LORD                                    = 8635,  -- What is this you speak? The Shadow Lord is being resurrected!?
        THIS_CANNOT_BE_WE_LL_HAVE_TO_REPORT                                       = 8636,  -- This cannot be! We'll have to report this to the royal family!
        I_SHALL_WRITE_AN_EPISTLE_I_WILL_NEED                                      = 8637,  -- I shall write an epistle. I will need you to deliver it posthaste to Monarlais Halver back in the motherland.
        YOU_MUST_PROTECT_THIS_LETTER_WITH_YOUR_LIFE                               = 8638,  -- You must protect this letter with your life. Now hurry and deliver it to San d'Oria!
        WHAT_ARE_YOU_DAWDLING_FOR_BOY_GIRL_DID                                    = 8639,  -- What are you dawdling for, boy/girl]? Did I not order you to hurry back to San d'Oria and pass my letter on to Halver, the Monarlais?
        CONSUL_MOURICES_S_FACE_HAS_BLANCHED_DID_YOU                               = 8640,  -- Consul Mourices's face has blanched. Did you say something to upset him? Did you not complete your mission correctly?
        THE_FEROCIOUS_MONSTER_WAS_REALLY_A_TRAP_SET                               = 8641,  -- The ferocious monster was really a trap set by the beastmen...? What a horrid turn of events this has proved to be.
        MOREOVER_THERE_IS_TALK_OF_A_NETHER_BEAST                                  = 8642,  -- Moreover, there is talk of a nether beast appearing? Could it be...? No! Do not tell me that we are marching forthright into another Great War?
        YOU_MENTIONED_THAT_WHEN_THE_NETHER_BEAST_APPEARED                         = 8643,  -- You mentioned that when the nether beast appeared, a Mithra guard came to your aid?
        THE_ONLY_MITHRA_WITH_THAT_DEGREE_OF_STRENGTH                              = 8644,  -- The only Mithra with that degree of strength would be one of the Sibyl Guards from Heavens Tower.
        PRODUCER_S_DEBUG_MENU_OPENING_EVENTS_MISSIONS_WARP                        = 8645,  -- PRODUCER'S DEBUG MENU... @OPENING EVENTS. MISSIONS. WARP. SAW OPENING EVENT. CHEAT THE FAME GAME. RESET ALLNITIALIZE. MissionEX.
        WARP_TO_MANUSTERY1_MANUSTERY2_WEAVERS_GUILD_BONEWORKERS_GUILD             = 8646,  -- WARP TO...? MANUSTERY1. MANUSTERY2. WEAVERS' GUILD. BONEWORKERS' GUILD. GOOD GOODS. AUCTION HOUSE. CHOCOBOSTABLES. CONSULATE OF SAN D'ORIA. EASTERN GATEHOUSE. APOTHECARY. MITHRA BOSS. CAT BURGLAR'S PAD. DHALMEL FARM.
        WHAT_YOU_WANT_TO_DO_RANK_QUEST_WARP                                       = 8647,  -- WHAT YOU WANT TO DO? @RANK. QUEST. WARP. ITEMS. QUEST TO BE HUNTER. LEFT ZONE ONCE. RESET ALL QUEST FLAGS. >INVESTIGATION. >YOU-KNOW-WHATS-ITS.
        WHICH_QUEST_UTE001_NEWJJV_QLA6V_H_MSNV_V                                  = 8648,  -- WHICH QUEST? ute001:NEWJJV-qLa6v %="H%&MsNv %%=#{%*v %Rv ukI001:NE%iRv %%cv %lmv uck003:A;V`%[%v
